  "prompt": "Do consulting firms show their consultants' transcripts to their clients?",
  "response": "Consulting firms typically do not show their consultants' academic transcripts to their clients. The focus in consulting is generally on the consultants' skills, experience, and track record rather than their academic grades. Clients usually assess consulting firms based on the firm's reputation, case studies, success stories, and the specific expertise of the consultants involved in the project. However, consultants may include their educational background along with other credentials in their professional profiles or resumes, which can be shared with clients if relevant to the engagement.",
